truth is a central theme of Michael Ondaatje's new novel, ``Anil's
Ghost,'' and was very much on his mind during a recent interview.
By Mel Gussow.
</P>
<P>
   CZECH-GLASS-ART (Zelezny Brod, Czech Republic) _ Nearly half a
century spent refining the art and the technique of casting huge
chunks of delicately colored glass, and a rare and genuinely
harmonious collaboration between husband and wife, underpin the
work of Stanislav Libensky and Jaroslava Brychtova, which is having
a major retrospective at the Heller Gallery in New York. By Peter
S. Green.
