   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FACTORY-KILLERS (San Leandro, Calif.) _ A sausage maker accused
of fatally shooting three food inspectors at his downtown factory
had grown furious with the government's scrutiny in recent months
and may have snapped, according to people who know him. By DEMIAN
BULWA, JIM HERRON ZAMORA and MATTHEW YI.
</P>
<P>
   NIKE-ASIA (San Francisco) _ The California Supreme Court has
agreed to decide whether a San Francisco activist can sue Nike Inc.
for allegedly lying about conditions in its Asian factories. The
suit attacks Nike's statements to the public and its stockholders
about its treatment of hundreds of thousands of workers, mostly
women, in contractors' Asian factories that make the company's
shoes and other apparel. By BOB EGELKO.
</P>
