   INTERNATIONAL NEWS (``I'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEXICAN-ELECTION (Mexico City) _ Francisco Labastida Ochoa has
been training for the Mexican presidency for much of his life. He
is a stalwart of the Institutional Revolutionary Party, which has
ruled Mexico since 1929, steadily climbing the ranks to hold some
of the highest posts in the government. He also is the first
candidate in modern Mexican history to face a bona fide challenge
for the country's highest office. By SUSANA HAYWARD.
</P>
