 &HT;    Finding diverse communities online
 &HT;    Omar L. Gallaga
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ www.aOnline.com _ Web portals catering to
specific ethnic groups are increasing in number, and some of them,
like aOnline.com, are creating hotbeds of online communities and
providing updated news and entertainment for monitories. This site,
catering to Asian-Americans, offers news, resources and original
columns.
</P>
<P>
   www.campchaos.com/cartoons/napsterbad _ Warning: lots and lots
of bad language here. This page features the extremely popular
animated cartoons featuring fictional incarnations of Metallica's
Lars Ulrich and James Hetfield railing against their mortal foe,
Napster. ``Napster _ Bad!'' is becoming a Web cult classic.
</P>
<P>
   www.mamma.com _ Search engines are notoriously flaky sometimes,
but mamma.com prides itself on accuracy. While that in itself is
probably not enough to earn a link, we can't help falling in love
with the site's mascot, a animated, matronly gray haired woman who
reminds us of Aunt Bea and the farmer's wife from the film,
``Babe.'' We love mamma.com, but more to the point, we love Mamma.
</P>
<P>
   ianrwww.unl.edu/ianr/pat/ephome.htm _ Pesticides have been in
the news lately, and this site, the University of Nebraska's
Pesticide Education Resources, has information on safety,
regulations, laws, agriculture and environmental protection.
</P>
