<P>
   SEAFOOD STIR-FRY WITH BASIL
</P>
<P>
   1 pound fresh mussels
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup chopped fresh hot chili
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons chopped fresh garlic
</P>
<P>
   5 Chinese black mushrooms, soaked until soft and cut into strips
</P>
<P>
   15 medium shrimp, shells removed, tails left on
</P>
<P>
   2 cups Thai basil leaves, stems removed and washed
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup green onion, cut into 1-inch long pieces
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon fish sauce
</P>
<P>
   Soak mussels in water for 4 hours. Wash shell and remove beard.
Add mussels to saucepan with no liquid, cover, cooked over medium
heat until mussels just open. Shake while cooking. Remove mussels
from shell.
</P>
<P>
   Add chopped fresh chili and fresh garlic to pan, stir for 30
seconds. Add mushrooms and stir for 30 seconds. Add shrimp and
mussels and cook until shrimp turn pink. Add Thai basil, green
onion, fish sauce. Stir thoroughly and serve.
</P>
