   ___
</P>
<P>
   CHINESE BROCCOLI WITH TOFU AND SOY SAUCE
</P>
<P>
   Vegetable oil, divided
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon fresh chopped garlic
</P>
<P>
   3 cups Chinese broccoli, cut into 1-inch long pieces
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup water
</P>
<P>
   1 pound firm tofu
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons oyster sauce
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon Thai soy sauce
</P>
<P>
   8 pieces fried dried chili pepper
</P>
<P>
   Squeeze excess water from tofu. Cut tofu into 1-by-1
1/2-by-1/2-inch pieces. Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.
</P>
<P>
   Heat 2 tablespoons oil. Add chopped garlic, stir until garlic is
light brown. Add Chinese broccoli, stir quickly for 3 minutes. Add
water and cook for 2 minutes. Add tofu and mix. Add oyster sauce,
soy sauce and mix well.
</P>
<P>
   Arrange on platter and garnish with fried chili pepper.
</P>
