<P>
   TOM YUM KOONG
</P>
<P>
   1 stalk lemon grass
</P>
<P>
   1 cup straw mushrooms
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup fish sauce
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons hot and sour soup base
</P>
<P>
   30 cherry tomatoes
</P>
<P>
   20 medium defrosted shrimp, peeled, tails left on
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup lime juice
</P>
<P>
   10 leaves cilantro
</P>
<P>
   Boil 1 gallon water. Chop bottom 6 inches of lemon grass into 2
(3-inch) pieces and crush. Add to boiling water. Add straw
mushrooms, fish sauce and soup base.
</P>
<P>
   Cut a plus sign in top of cherry tomatoes and add to soup 10
minutes before serving. Add shrimp and cook until they turn pink.
Add lime juice, serve in bowls and garnish with cilantro.
</P>
