<P>
   VEGETABLE DELIGHT
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons peanut oil
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon chopped fresh garlic
</P>
<P>
   6 Chinese black mushrooms, soaked until soft, remove stems and
cut into strips
</P>
<P>
   1/3 julienne-cut gingerroot
</P>
<P>
   2 cups snow peas with ends removed
</P>
<P>
   2 cups red bell pepper, chunked
</P>
<P>
   2 cups yellow bell pepper, chunks
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons oyster sauce
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon Thai soy sauce
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon black pepper
</P>
<P>
   Heat peanut oil until hot. Add garlic and stir for 30 seconds.
Add black mushrooms and stir for 30 seconds. Add gingerroot and
stir quickly. Add snow peas, peppers, 2 tablespoons water and stir
for 1 minute. Add oyster sauce and soy sauce, stir quickly. Arrange
on platter and garnish with black pepper.
</P>
