<P>
   CHICKEN RED CURRY WITH NOODLES
</P>
<P>
   2 bunches Oriental noodles
</P>
<P>
   12 ounces coconut milk, divided
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 tablespoons red curry paste
</P>
<P>
   2 cups boneless, skinless chicken breast, cut into chunks
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup fish sauce
</P>
<P>
   10 Thai eggplants, stemmed and quartered
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup long green hot pepper, thinly sliced on the diagonal
</P>
<P>
   1 cup Thai basil leaves
</P>
<P>
   Bring a large pot of salted water to boil. Add noodles, cook and
stir until al dente. Drain; rinse with cold water and immerse in
cold water. Form into coils, 6 noodles to a coil, and squeeze out
excess water. arrange on plate.
</P>
<P>
   Add 3/4 cup coconut milk to a saucepan and bring to a boil. Add
red curry paste and blend. Add chicken and fish sauce and stir. Add
remaining coconut milk and 3 cups water, simmer until chicken is
cooked through.
</P>
<P>
   Add eggplant, hot pepper and basil and bring to a boil. Serve in
a bowl with noodles on the side.
</P>
<P>
