</P>
<P>
   DEEP FRIED TOFU WITH SWEET AND SOUR SAUCE
</P>
<P>
   10 pounds extra firm tofu
</P>
<P>
   Vegetable oil for deep frying
</P>
<P>
   2 cups spicy sweet and sour sauce
</P>
<P>
   1 cup vinegar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup water
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup chopped fresh cilantro leaves
</P>
<P>
   Squeeze excess water from tofu and let dry at room temperature
for 2 hours. Cut in bite-size pieces.
</P>
<P>
   Heat oil over medium-high heat for deep frying. Fry tofu pieces
until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
</P>
<P>
   Combine sweet and sour sauce, vinegar and water and bring to a
boil over high heat. Add the chopped cilantro and simmer for 3
minutes. Let cool before serving.
</P>
<P>
   Serve tofu with sauce on the side.
</P>
