   SEAFOOD SALAD
</P>
<P>
   20 shrimp, defrosted and shelled
</P>
<P>
   1 pound bay scallops
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup yellow onion, sliced into very thin rings
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup thinly sliced lemon grass
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup mint leaves
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon chopped fresh garlic
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons chopped fresh red chili
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup fish sauce
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup lime juice
</P>
<P>
   Lettuce leaves
</P>
<P>
   Boil water and cook shrimp and scallops until tender. Drain
seafood and place in mixing bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Add onion, lemon grass and mint to seafood. Combine garlic,
chili, fish sauce, sugar and lime juice and add to seafood. Stir
thoroughly. Serve on a bed of lettuce.
</P>
