<P>
   BEEF SALAD
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 pounds trimmed flank steak
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons chopped fresh garlic
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup yellow onion, thinly sliced
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup lime juice
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup fish sauce
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon ground roasted chili
</P>
<P>
   3 lettuce leaves
</P>
<P>
   10 cilantro leaves
</P>
<P>
   Grill flank steak until rare and slice into thin strips. Mix
with garlic and onion and set aside.
</P>
<P>
   In a separate bowl, combine lime juice, fish sauce and sugar and
mix well. Combine with beef mixture. Add ground chili and mix well.
Serve on a bed of lettuce, garnished with cilantro.
</P>
