</P>
<P>
   NADER-LABOR (Washington) _ Ralph Nader, the longtime consumer
advocate who is mounting a surprisingly potent presidential
campaign, met Thursday with the head of the Teamsters union, who
lavished huge praise on him as the only candidate really trying to
protect America's unionized work force. Of course Hoffa's words are
directed as much at Al Gore as they are at Ralph Nader, and
Democrats and Gore advisers are growing increasingly worried about
Nader's rising strength and his alliances within labor. By Richard
L. Berke.
