as perhaps the world's most ruthlessly efficient rebel force, were
forged into a tiny but lethal body of fighters by a cultish leader
whose face has been seen by few. He ruthlessly killed off other
Tamils who didn't accept his leadership, and now his fighters are
threatening to defeat a force 30 times larger in Sri Lanka's bloody
17-year civil war. By Indira A.R. Lakshmanan. 1630 words.
