aid of nearly $1 billion to help Colombia fight the illegal drug
trade that is fueling a bloody guerrilla conflict and sending
cocaine and heroin into U.S. cities. The aid was approved as part
of a $13.4 billion foreign operations spending bill, which passed
with overwhelming bipartisan support in a vote of 95-4. (Summary
from wires) By Eric Schmitt.
</P>
