   TEXAS-HEALTH (Washington) _ In a major test case, a federal
appeals court has upheld a Texas law that allows patients to sue
health maintenance organizations in state court for medical
malpractice. The decision came this week as the 5th U.S. Circuit
Court of Appeals, in New Orleans, ruled on the first of a new wave
of state laws expanding the legal liability of HMOs. The ruling was
not a complete victory for either patients or insurance companies.
By Robert Pear.
</P>
<P>
   CONGRESS-CAMPAIGN (Washington) _ The House Ways and Means
Committee is expected to approve a broad financial disclosure bill
requiring a range of groups that conduct political activities to
disclose their donors. Developing. By Eric Schmitt.
