<HEADLINE>
ASK THE TRAVEL EXPERT 
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
  ATTENTION EDITORS: The following material from The New York Times
Syndicate is for use by WAY TO GO! clients. Nonsubscribers can use
this article only by special arrangement. For purchase information,
see end of text. 
 &HT;    
 (PLEASE NOTE: The word AT in parentheses has been used in an e-mail
address instead of the symbol, which many computer systems at
newspapers can't interpret.)  
 &HT;    
 By WILLIAM T. TOMICKI 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
 &HT;     Q:  My department at work is in charge of arranging our annual
regional conference, and we don't want to repeat last year's
disaster _ too hot, too many bugs and too many guests at the hotel.
Plus, I know that many of my co-workers would like to bring their
families. Do you know of a resort that can accommodate us in
comfort?
 &HT;     A:  One of the best places I can recommend is the Marriott
Resort &AMP; Golf Club on Marco Island in South Florida. This resort
has mastered the art of having something for everyone.
 &HT;    The resort boasts over 40,000 square feet of meeting space
spread over seven outdoor function areas and three large, versatile
ballrooms.
 &HT;    You can also make use of the in-house production company, Wizard
Studios International, to design events that are suited to your
company's needs. After hours, your co-workers can take advantage of
one of the many lounges and restaurants.
 &HT;    The resort offers daily activities _ from sailing and shelling
excursions to parasailing, kayaking and windsurfing _ that take
advantage of the miles of shimmering white sand beach and the
tranquil blue-green Gulf waters. The 18-hole championship golf
course makes good use of the natural landscape.
 &HT;    Guests can also use the 16-court tennis complex, the health club
and spa options, island bike tours, and the three pools and
whirlpool. For kids, there are daily Kids Korner activities;
ping-pong tables; an arcade; and, on weekends, the ``Dive-In,''
where, instead of sitting in cars, they can watch movies while
floating in the pool.
 &HT;    It's easy to see why the Marco Island Marriott Resort &AMP; Golf
Club has won numerous awards for its full-service meeting and
convention properties as well as being named one of ``America's Top
20 Resorts'' by Conde Nast Traveler. For more information and
reservations, call (800) GET-HERE or (941) 394-2511.
 &HT;     Q:  Can you tell me if the Plaza Hotel in New York City is
really as special and luxurious as people say it is?
 &HT;     A:  Luxurious indulgence is what you'll find at the unsurpassed
Plaza Hotel. The Plaza has delighted young and old with memorable
stays for generations.
 &HT;    Located between Central Park and Fifth Avenue, The Plaza is both
contemporary and chic, yet exudes great charm. Highly attentive
service and attention to detail are hallmarks of this legend.
 &HT;    Rooms and suites are spacious, have exceptional high ceilings
and capture the feeling of old European charm. As an added bonus,
computers are available in all rooms and suites, and a beautiful,
8,000-square-foot spa and workout room are now open.
 &HT;    The Plaza is in a class by itself, and General Manager Gary
Schweikert plans to keep it that way. Room rates vary according to
season. Double rooms range in cost from $275 to $725; suites, $500
to $15,000. For reservations and more information, call (800)
527-4727.
 &HT;     Q:  My best friend and I are looking for a good golf package in
Las Vegas. Have you heard of any lately?
 &HT;     A:  The Golden Nugget, located in the heart of downtown Las
Vegas, is offering an amazing golf package that starts at $183.15
for two people. In addition to the room, the price includes green
fees, golf cart, tee times, bag storage and tax.
 &HT;    The Golden Nugget is ideal for quick-and-easy trips to
outstanding local golf courses, such as American Golf's Badlands
Golf Club, Las Vegas National Golf Course, Painted Desert Golf
Course and the Wildhorse Golf Club.
 &HT;    Guests are free to enjoy the amenities that the Golden Nugget, a
recipient of the AAA Four Diamond award, offers. The resort boasts
breathtaking views, first-class rooms and suites, live
entertainment, shopping, several dining options and a luxury spa
and salon. For more information or reservations, call (800)
846-5336.
 &HT;     Q:  I recently completed an extensive family tree and
discovered that I am distantly related to Austrian royalty. As a
result, I will soon be visiting this country to learn more about my
heritage. Do you know of any museums or day tours there that place
an emphasis on Austrian history?
 &HT;     A:  Even better, why don't you discover what it felt like to be
Austrian royalty by spending a few nights in a 12th-century
medieval Austrian castle? The Schloss Matzen bed and breakfast is
located in the Alpbach Valley, just 30 minutes east of Innsbruck.
Here, guests are transported back in time as soon as they set foot
behind the heavy stone walls and into the medieval ambience of the
local antique decor.
 &HT;    The small community of the Alpbach Valley celebrates its local
cuisine, music, festivals and customs, which are sure to give you
plenty of insight into the lives of your Austrian ancestors.
 &HT;    For more information, call Schloss Matzen at (888) 837-0618, or
visit http://www.schlossmatzen.com
 &HT;    This unique hotel _ and others like it _ can be found in the
Spring/Summer 2000 Specialty Travel Index, which costs $10 per year
for two issues. Send orders to info(AT)specialitytravel.com.
 &HT;     Q:  My fiancee and I are looking for an escape from reality. We
want to eat well, pamper ourselves and feel like the world is a
million miles away. Please help us find a luxe hideaway.
 &HT;     A:  The ultraluxe and secluded Little Palm Island is exactly
what you are looking for. Located three miles offshore in the
Florida Keys, this island hideaway is only accessible by boat or
seaplane.
 &HT;    This Relais and Chateaux property is also offering an amazing
couples package through Sept. 30, 2000. The Island Indulgence
package includes four nights/five days accommodations, a welcome
bottle of wine, three gourmet meals daily, one ``hot stone''
massage per person, a daylong snorkel trip, a private sunset
cruise, tax, gratuity and airport transfers. The package is priced
at $4,790 per couple.
 &HT;    The absence of everyday nuisances, such as telephones and
televisions, at Little Palm Island make it perfect for couples who
want to spend quality time together. Whether soaking up some sun on
the beach or relaxing in your bungalow, you are sure to feel
removed from the everyday grind.
 &HT;    Also, don't miss a visit to the full-service spa, featuring
professional therapists and ecologically balanced Pevonia Botanica
products. 
 &HT;    
 &HT;    Readers are invited to submit questions to William Tomicki, P.O.
Box 5148, Santa Barbara, Calif. 93150. Although he cannot answer
each query individually, selected questions will be included in his
column. Mr. Tomicki, who logs over 150,000 miles each year, is the
publisher of ENTREE, a travel newsletter. 
 &HT;    
 c.2000 William T. Tomicki 
