<HEADLINE>
SHOPPING AROUND: ALL-AMERICAN ADVENTURES  
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
  ATTENTION EDITORS: The following material from The New York Times
Syndicate is for use by WAY TO GO! clients. Nonsubscribers can use
this article only by special arrangement. For purchase information,
see end of text. 
 &HT;    
 (Color slide included.) 
 By EVERETT POTTER 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
 &HT;    From the Green Mountains of Vermont to the Sonoran Desert of
Arizona, the United States has plenty of vacation destinations for
adventurous travelers. Here's a sampling of trips for early fall.
Prices are per person, based on double occupancy, and land-only
unless otherwise noted.
 &HT;     Butterfield &AMP; Robinson  (70 Bond St., Toronto, Ontario, Canada
M5B 1X3; 800-678-1147; www.butterfield.com) has a ``Smoky Mountains
Getaway Walking'' trip, a five-day adventure that features a stay
at Blackberry Farm, a Relais &AMP; Chateaux property. Walkers also get
to spend the night in a luxury camp, when they're not walking past
the magnolia trees and red maples of the Great Smokies. The
September departure costs $3,695.
 &HT;    For the yachting set, the ``America's Cup Getaway Bike, Walk &AMP;
Sail'' is a five-day trip to Newport, Martha's Vineyard and
Nantucket. This trip combines biking and walking with sailing on
12-meter racing yachts. The September departure is $4,995.
 &HT;     Country Walkers  (P.O. Box 180, Waterbury, Vt. 05676;
800-464-9255; www.countrywalkers.com) has ``Utah: Natural Temples
of Zion and Bryce.'' During this six-day walk, which departs in
September and October, travelers stay in classic canyon lodges.
Equal time is spent exploring the crimson-colored cliffs of Zion
and the limestone formations in Bryce. The cost is $1,879.
 &HT;    The company also offers ``Arizona: Riches of the Sonoran
Desert.'' This seven-day trip visits Ramsey, Madera and Sabino
Canyons, as well as the Chiricahua Mountains. Exotic plant life and
wildlife are highlights of this trip. There are September and
October departures, and the cost is $1,969.
 &HT;     Equitour  (P.O. Box 807, Dubois, Wyo. 82513; 800-545-0019;
www.ridingtours.com) has a seven-day ``Redwood Coast Ride'' along
the coast of California that goes through Jackson State Forest and
includes a ride along 10 Mile Beach. In fact, much of the time is
spent riding on northern California's beaches.
 &HT;    Departures are in September and October, and the cost is $1,795.
This trip is perfect for intermediate riders, who can expect
upwards of five hours a day of riding.
 &HT;    Beginners might enjoy the ``Green Mountain Inn to Inn Ride.''
Timed for participants to enjoy foliage season in September, the
six-day ride is $1,650 and goes through Vermont's lakes region.
Riders stay in period inns and can expect to spend five to six
hours in the saddle daily.
 &HT;     New England Hiking Holidays  (P.O. Box 1648, North Conway, N.H.
03860; 800-869-0949; www.nehikingholidays.com) has a five-day trip
called ``North Carolina: Blue Ridge Mountains'' that follows the
route of the Blue Ridge Parkway. Hikers go through Moses Cone
National Park and have the option of ascending Grandfather
Mountain. There are departures in October, and the cost is $1,175.
 &HT;    ``Virginia: Shenandoah Mountains'' is a five-day hike through
Shenandoah National Park and the Blue Ridge Mountains. Highlights
include ascents of two, 4,000-foot peaks _ Mount Pleasant and Mount
Pompey. The cost is $1,175, and there are departures in October.
 &HT;     The Northwest Passage  (1130 Greenleaf Ave., Wilmette, Ill.
60091; 800-RECREATE; www.nwpassage.com) does international
destinations such as Crete and the North Pole, but it also focuses
on perhaps the most overlooked area in the United States for
adventure travel: the Midwest.
 &HT;    Their ``Isle Royale-Lake Superior'' trip is an eight-day
sea-kayaking voyage. The trip to the island, located 22 miles
offshore, offers what the company says is ``the most realistic
sealike destination for sea kayakers in the Midwest.'' This camping
trip runs in September and costs $825.
 &HT;    The ``Porcupine Mountains-Michigan'' is a four-day
hiking/camping trip to the Upper Peninsula of Michigan. The cost
for the September departure is $295.
 &HT;    River Odysseys West (P.O. Box 579, Coeur d'Alene, Idaho 83816;
800-451-6034; www.rowinc.com) offers a large number of western
rafting trips, although most of them will be completed by midsummer
due to water levels.
 &HT;    The exception is the five-day ``Snake Rmidsummerlls Canyon''
trip, which takes rafters through the deepest river gorge in North
America, Hells Canyon. On the border with Oregon and Idaho, the
river offers some of the largest rapids in the Northwest. There are
departures in September, from $995.
 &HT;     VBT  (P.O. Box 711, Bristol, Vt. 05443; 800-245-3868;
www.vbt.com) does the ``Lake Champlain Valley'' of Vermont for six
days in September and October. This is a biking trip, with an
optional half-day of sea kayaking on Lake Champlain, which lies
between the Adironadacks and the Green Mountains.
 &HT;    There are routes for varying abilities and an itinerary that
includes stops at such towns as East Middlebury. The cost is
$1,145.
 &HT;    The ``Purely Acadia'' trip is just that _ six days exploring
Acadia National Park. Most biking is done on the car-less carriage
roads that John D. Rockefeller built throughout the park. But there
are also trips to Swans Island and Little Cranberry Island. The
cost for the September departures is $1,395.
 &HT;     The Wayfarers  (172 Bellevue Ave., Newport, R.I. 02840;
800-249-4620; www.thewayfarers.com) offers a ``New Mexico: Land of
Enchantment'' trip, a six-day walk based in Taos and Santa Fe.
Walkers go to Abiquiu and the home of painter Georgia O'Keefe,
visit the Taos pueblo and wander through Frjoles Canyon. The cost
is $1,695, and there are departures in October.
 &HT;    The Wayfarers also have a ``Coast of Maine'' trip. Moving up the
coast, by van and by foot, travelers visit Damariscotta Mills and
explore the area around Camden and Rockport. The cost for this
September departure is $1,695. 
 ---- 
 c.2000 Everett Potter 
