<HEADLINE>
SHARK SAFETY TIPS
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies SHARK ATTACKS) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ Stay in groups. Sharks are more likely to attack a solitary
person.
</P>
<P>
   _ Avoid being in the water during twilight or darkness, when
sharks are most active.
</P>
<P>
   _ Do not go into the water if you're bleeding.
</P>
<P>
   _ Avoid shiny jewelry. It resembles the sheen of fish.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sharks see contrast particularly well. Avoid uneven tanning
and bright-colored swimsuits that contrast with your skin.
</P>
<P>
   _ Don't splash a lot.
</P>
<P>
   _ Don't let pets in the water, because their erratic movements
may attract sharks.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hangouts for sharks are between two sandbars and near steep
dropoffs.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
