<P>
   DIESEL-POLLUTION _ ATLANTA _ A variety of environmental groups
on Thursday told the EPA that proposed regulations to drastically
reduce pollution from diesel trucks and buses is the most
significant step to cut vehicle emissions since the removal of lead
from gasoline. Speaking at a public hearing in Atlanta on the new
rules, the groups urged the EPA to withstand efforts by the oil
industry to weaken the rules. Oil industry spokesmen said the new
rules will greatly drive up the cost of diesel fuel and trucking
costs. However, the automotive industry say they are all for the
rules. (Seabrook, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 17.
</P>
