   EDITORIAL-HATE _ No sooner did legislation expanding federal
jurisdiction over hate crimes clear one congressional hurdle than
it faces another. it's tough going, but the struggle is worth it to
cover crimes motivated by animus toward gays, the handicapped and
victims of the other sex. (The Atlanta Constitution). 7.
</P>
