   MOVIES-IRENE _ Movie review: ``Me, Myself &AMP; Irene'' with Jim
Carrey and Renee Zellweger. Like ``There's Something About Mary,''
it's an embarrassingly funny movie built on beautifully
constructed, crude jokes. But it's also embarrassingly weak on
story. Grade: B-. (StMurray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-CROUPIER _ Review of the movie,''Croupier.'' It's a
cerebral exercise in paranoia, as a casino dealer gets in over his
head trying to aid a damsel in distress. Two and one-half stars.
(Erstein, Palm Beach Post). 16.
</P>
