<SLUG> BC-SHARKATTACKS-ODDS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE ODDS OF GETTING ATTACKED BY A SHARK
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies SHARK ATTACKS) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Shark bites: What are the odds?
</P>
<P>
   Shark facts from the International Shark Attack File, a division
of the Florida Museum of Natural History, University of Florida:
</P>
<P>
   _ Human-bites-human reports: about 1,580 a year in the United
States.
</P>
<P>
   _ Shark-bites-human reports: about 11 a year in the United
States.
</P>
<P>
   _ The International Shark Attack File claims home improvement is
a more dangerous pastime that swimming among the sharks. As an
example, it cites the year 1996, when the U.S. Consumer Product
Safety Commission reported 43,687 people were somehow injured by
toilets. More than 36,000 people were injured while pruning. More
than 10,000 were injured by buckets. And only 18 by sharks.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
