<P>
   BLESSED RETREATS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGANI, Italy _ In a small town in southern Italy near Pompeii,
we paid just $22 apiece for a double room with private bath,
breakfast of bread, coffee and fresh fruit, and a four-course
dinner with wine. How'd we find such a bargain? By doing what
European tourists, especially in Italy, have done for years _ we
stayed in a monastery. Hundreds of Italian religious institutions
offer rooms and, often, meals, to guests, and American travelers
are finally catching on. By PATRICIA RODRIGUEZ. Story has moved in
``t'' travel category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
