religious leaders will hold a national conference on ``Whiteness''
at Simmons College. They are part of the burgeoning field of
``white studies,'' a kind of extension of the academic take on
``African American studies'' or ``women's studies.'' Others wonder
if this is an example of academics who've gone off the deep end. By
Tatsha Robertson. 900 words.
</P>
