<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, JUNE 23
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-NY-EGAN-INSTALL-NYT (moved on Monday, June 19)  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, June 19,
about Archbishop Edward M. Egan's Mass of Installation and an
article on Sunday about preparations for the ceremony both
misstated the route of an outdoor procession in Manhattan. Before
walking to St. Patrick's Cathedral for the Mass on Monday, more
than 1,000 priests and bishops assembled at the Palace Hotel,
behind the cathedral on Madison Avenue, not at the Catholic Center
at 56th Street and First Avenue.
</P>
<P>
   BC-DOT-COM-LAYOFFS-NYT (moved on Wednesday, June 21) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, June
21, about recent layoffs at Internet companies misstated the status
of one company, APBnews.com. Although it announced on June 5 that
it was out of money and was laying off all 140 employees, it has
continued operations, recently found new financing and hired back
about 30 workers.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-BENSON-NYT (moved on Wednesday, June 21) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   An obituary of Mary Benson sent by the New York Times News
Service on Wednesday, June 21, misstated the title of one of her
books. It is ``Athol Fugard and Barney Simon: Bare Stage, a Few
Props, Great Theater,'' not ``Athol Fugard and Barney Smith.''  &QL; 
 &QL; 
