 &UR; REEL: &LR;  It started simply, &LR;  with a guy who really loved movies. He
scribbled his film recommendations on note cards and stuffed them
into videotape boxes in the small video-rental store he opened in
the mid-80s. Fast forward a decade. From that decidedly low-tech
beginning, Stuart Skorman blazed a trail as an e-commerce pioneer,
founding video seller Reel.com. The company became a market leader,
was sold for a jaw-dropping sum of money, then proceeded to lose an
equally jaw-dropping sum. And last week, Reel.com had the plug
pulled on its e-commerce operations and laid off most of its staff,
