<HEADLINE>
WINSTON WEST FOCUSES ON L.A.
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEITH LAIR  
 c.2000 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRWINDALE, Calif. _ Racing three times on one track in one
season has not been unusual for the NASCAR Winston West Series, but
running at Irwindale Speedway three times this year is vital,
series spokesman Kevin Green says.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is a very important market for us,'' Green said. ``And
aside from the market, we have a number of teams from here. So,
it's important.''
</P>
<P>
   The half-mile oval at Mesa Marin has hosted three events in one
year three times, between 1994 and '96. This year, the Bakersfield
track has two NWWS races and Irwindale has three _ two Home Depot
250s, Saturday and Aug. 19, and the season-ending Home Depot 300 on
Nov. 11.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's also important to our sponsors,'' Green said. ``L.A. is a
very important market to us.''
</P>
<P>
   Other than last year's sell-out opening night and Turkey Night
Grand Prix, the two NWWS events drew the largest attendance numbers
last year at Irwindale. In those races, Steve Portegna and Austin
Cameron both won their first NWWS races.
</P>
<P>
   The Turkey Night Grand Prix is the track's biggest open-wheel
event and the NWWS races are the biggest NASCAR events.
</P>
<P>
   ``Here, we look at this as our Winston Cup (race),'' track
marketing director Pat Patterson said.
</P>
<P>
   __ The particulars: Twenty-six cars will race for a total of
$116,991. Twenty-one cars will qualify through two-lap time trials,
two spots will be awarded based on point standings, two on owner
point standings and one to the NWWS champion.
</P>
<P>
   Gates open at 4 p.m., with time trials starting at 4:30 p.m. An
autograph session will be at 6:30 p.m., with the Super Late Model
trophy dash at 7 p.m. The NWWS race is scheduled for a 7:45 p.m.
start and the 75-lap Super Late Model race will follow the NWWS
show. Speedvision will tape the NWWS race. It will be broadcast
July 15 at 5 p.m. and July 17 at 11 a.m.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
