<P>
   Approval by the Senate Governmental Organization Committee on
Tuesday brought California closer to legal telephone and Internet
wagering. The bill must get past an appropriations committee, the
full Senate and Assembly and Gov. Gray Davis in order to take
effect Jan. 1. . . . Not surprisingly, racing fans don't think
Tiger Woods' 15-stroke U.S. Open victory is the most dominating
sports performance of all time. In an NTRA.com poll, they chose
Secretariat's 31-length Belmont Stakes win (64 percent) and Mark
Spitz's seven swimming gold medals (9 percent) over Woods' runaway
(8 percent) and Wilt Chamberlain's 100-point game (8 percent). . .
. Today completes Corey Nakatani's three-day suspension for a
riding infraction June 16. . . . No racing Wednesday, June 28,
preceding a six-day stretch of racing that includes Monday, July 3,
and Tuesday, July 4. . . .
</P>
<P>
   Russell Baze won his 22nd Golden Gate riding championship and
Jerry Hollendorfer won his 20th consecutive Golden Gate training
title as the track wrapped up its season Sunday. The Northern
California fairs season opened Wednesday at Stockton. . . . A
quarterhorse version of Oak Tree's California Cup and Hollywood
Park's California Gold Rush debuts Saturday at Los Alamitos. It's a
night of existing Cal-bred stakes with purses totaling $1 million.
. . . Rarity: The horses in Hollywood Park's seventh race Thursday
finished in the order of their post positions and program numbers.
No. 1, Hope Island, paid $9.60 to win.
